com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.managers

Class ManagersRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<T>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.PaginatedRequestExecutor<Managers>
        • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.managers.ManagersRequestExecutor

  • public class ManagersRequestExecutor
extends PaginatedRequestExecutor<Managers>
    Request executor provided by ManagersApi. Use this class if you want to fetch managers through fluent API in chained fashion, for example: 
       
   IKontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloud.newInstance();
   Managers managers = kontaktCloud.managers().fetch()
      .subordinatesOf(supervisorID)
      .execute();
